g.aria-label: Subtitle text 'Gross domestic product (GDP) per capita measures the value of everything produced in a country during a year, divided by the number of people. The unit is in purchasing power parities (PPP dollars), fixed to 2017 prices. Data is adjusted for inflation and differences in the cost of living between countries.'

text.tspan: Gross domestic product (GDP) per capita measures the value of everything
produced in a country during a year, divided by the number of people.
The unit is in purchasing power parities (PPP dollars), fixed to 2017 prices.
Data is adjusted for inflation and differences in the cost of living between countries.
